Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Put
the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and halve the
@radishes{100%g}. Halve any large @cauliflower florets{300%g}. Pop the radish and cauliflower
onto another baking tray and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1%tbsp} and toss to coat. Roast on the middle
shelf of your oven until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While everything roasts, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and
thinly sliced). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Finely chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1%sprig}(finely chopped) (use stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g}
and dry-fry, stirring occasionally, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer the toasted almonds to a #bowl{}. Pop your pan back on medium heat with a drizzle
of @olive oil{}. When hot, add the red onion and cook until soft and sweet, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Turn down the heat if necessary.

Meanwhile, pop the @chives{1%tbsp}(finely chopped) in another small bowl with the lemon
zest, @olive oil{15%ml} for the drizzle and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and add more oil if you want the drizzle a bit looser. Set aside.

Once the onion is soft, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the
@balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and cook until evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in the
@water{75%ml} for the lentils and stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the
boil and simmer until reduced by half.

Stir the lentils into the pan and cook until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and add
@salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. When the cauliflower and radish are roasted, drizzle with
the @honey{15%ml}.

Serve the lentils in bowls with the roasted veg on top. Spoon over the drizzle and finish
with a sprinkling of toasted almonds. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!